# System Walkthrough - Large-Scale AI Document Processing System

I have successfully implemented the "foundation to roof" roadmap for your AI system. This local platform is designed to leverage your Ryzen 9 9900X and RTX 5060 Ti to process millions of documents.

## Architecture Overview

The system follows a microservices architecture coordinated by Kafka and stored in MinIO/Delta Lake:

```mermaid
graph TD
    User([User]) --> Frontend[Streamlit Dashboard]
    Frontend --> Ingestion[FastAPI Ingestion]
    Ingestion --> MinIO[(MinIO S3)]
    Ingestion --> Kafka{Kafka}
    Kafka --> Spark[PySpark Factory]
    Spark --> OCR[PaddleOCR GPU]
    OCR --> Delta[(Delta Lake)]
    User --> Chat[AI Chat UI]
    Chat --> RAG[RAG Service]
    RAG --> Milvus[(Milvus Vector DB)]
    RAG --> Llama[Local Llama-3]
    RAG --> Delta
```

## Implemented Components

### 1. Infrastructure Foundation
- [docker-compose.yaml](file:///home/alida/Documents/Cursor/Bigdata/infra/docker-compose.yaml): Deploys MinIO, Milvus, Postgres, Redis, Kafka, and Keycloak.
- [docker-compose-monitoring.yaml](file:///home/alida/Documents/Cursor/Bigdata/monitoring/docker-compose-monitoring.yaml): Deploys Prometheus, Grafana, and ELK stack.

### 2. Microservices
- [Ingestion Service](file:///home/alida/Documents/Cursor/Bigdata/services/ingestion/main.py): FastAPI handles file uploads to MinIO and emits Kafka events.
- [Processing Factory](file:///home/alida/Documents/Cursor/Bigdata/services/processing/spark_processor.py): PySpark listens to Kafka, uses PaddleOCR (GPU-ready) for text bóc tách, and saves to Delta Lake.
- [AI/RAG Service](file:///home/alida/Documents/Cursor/Bigdata/services/rag/rag_pipeline.py): Uses BGE-M3 embeddings, Milvus search, and LangChain with local Llama-3 (8B).

### 3. User Interface
- [Streamlit Frontend](file:///home/alida/Documents/Cursor/Bigdata/frontend/app.py): A unified dashboard for document management and a ChatGPT-style RAG interface.

## How to Get Started

1.  **Fix Docker Daemon**: I noticed a connection issue with your local Docker daemon. Please ensure Docker is running.
2.  **Run Setup**:
    ```bash
    chmod +x setup.sh
    ./setup.sh
    ```
3.  **Start Services**:
    - **Infrastructure**: `docker compose -f infra/docker-compose.yaml up -d`
    - **Backend**:
        ```bash
        python services/ingestion/main.py &
        python services/processing/spark_processor.py &
        python services/rag/rag_pipeline.py &
        ```
    - **Frontend**: `streamlit run frontend/app.py`

## Next Steps: Datasets
For testing with ~100GB of data, use the Hugging Face links mentioned in your roadmap:
- **RVL-CDIP**: `huggingface.co/datasets/rvl_cdip` (37GB)
- **IIT-CDIP**: `huggingface.co/datasets/pierreguillou/iit-cdip-1000-samples`

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Since you have an RTX 5060 Ti, ensure you have the NVIDIA Container Toolkit installed so the OCR service can access the GPU.
